As at 30 Oct 2014, the 20 minute version of the full length film has been viewed 555 times (75% of these were in the UK). It was also available to view as individual clips: 
? Part 1, including the introduction and a discussion of the benefits of HE has been viewed 125 times (67% of views were in the UK)
? Part 2 on funding 105 times (53% of views in the UK)
? Part 3 on cross border flow of students 55 times (84% of views in UK)
? Part 4 on widening access 81 times (80% of views in UK)
? Part 5 on young people's views of independence has been viewed 1,295 times (70% of views in UK)

Youtube analytics show that the clips have been viewed predominantly in the UK, but that they have also had substantial reach outside of the UK. Almost half (47%) of views of Part 2 on funding were from outside the UK, while 30% of Part 5 views were from outside the UK. Reach outside of the UK has also been significant, with clips viewed in 53 countries: France, Germany, Austria, Sweden, the USA, Switzerland, Belgium, Italy, Australia, Norway, Spain, the Netherlands, Canada, Portugal, Ukraine, Ireland, Mexico, Denmark, Latvia, India, United Arab Emirates, Israel, Estonia, Cyprus, Serbia, Malaysia, Slovakia, Luxembourg, Jamaica, Japan, Taiwan, Bangladesh, Singapore, Hong Kong, Brazil, Indonesia, Turkey, Tunisia, Poland, Peru, Chile, Philippines, Azerbaijan, Croatia, Nepal, South Korea, Sweden, Bulgaria, Slovenia, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Vietnam and Greece. The clip of the full film reached the widest selection of countries outside of the UK (38 in total). 

Youtube analytics show that views of Part 5 on young people's views of the referendum increased greatly between 31st August and 24 September 2014, when the clip received 603 views, with the greatest number of views received on one day (72) on the 17th September, implying it was being used as a resource by people during the referendum. 

