The literature review is covered under item 2 of the General Comments: 
'2. We note the references to SFC in the paper knowing what works in widening access. However, we would note that this can be challenging. Universities Scotland commissioned a literature review (jointly funded by SFC) Widening Access to Higher Education: Does Anyone Know What Works? , which identified some difficulties with determining what works, both because of limited evidence, research and evaluation, but also because of the multi-faceted nature of many interventions. This is further compounded by long lead in times for many projects from initial engagement. In addition, SFC (and predecessor bodies) has been looking at widening access for at least ten years without an agreed standard of what works in widening access and therefore the references in the Access and Inclusion Committee paper to 'best' and 'worst' are not appropriate.'</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>543fbbc9e64124.14278112</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:type>Citation in other policy documents</gtr:type><gtr:url>http://www.universities-scotland.ac.uk/uploads/WideningAccessToHE-CREID.pdf</gtr:url></gtr:policyInfluenceOutput><gtr:policyInfluenceOutput><gtr:areas/><gtr:description>Citation of Sarah Minty's paper to BERA 2015 in a report by the Social Mobility and child Poverty Commission</gtr:description><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>AFD3F57E-DAF5-4144-BB81-3ED81C9001DB</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>56ab7a2d40fe90.98326647</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:type>Citation in other policy documents</gtr:type><gtr:url>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/485926/State_of_the_nation_2015__social_mobility_and_child_poverty_in_Great_Britain.pdf</gtr:url></gtr:policyInfluenceOutput><gtr:policyInfluenceOutput><gtr:areas/><gtr:description>Citation of Susan Whittaker's evidence paper to the Welsh Government's call for evidence in Diamond Committee's interim report</gtr:description><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>BF71937C-CEF7-40B6-9F60-EB7B8E9B15E6</gtr:id><gt